race.description: Kym Thomas - Life Member E&G Handicap
race.comment: MAJOR RUMBLE (9) has shaped like a coming winner in both runs back, looming strongly but just lacking the finishing punch. Now third-up and peaking, he should slot in beautifully from the middle draw and be right in the thick of it again. STREETCAR APOLLO (3) resumes without a public jump-out but brings ample early speed and secures the key booking of Toeroek, which is a strong lead. Must be taken seriously. PANTOJA (5) resumes and makes his stable debut for the Hickmott yard after two sharp jumpouts. Any market push would be significant. PURFECT LINE (7) profiles well third-up and backs up quickly, though he may be forced a long way back from the wide alley. Still worth including. ALL SHOT (11) was a real flashing light late last start and can sneak into the frame again if the race shape suits. A value player.
